WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.002
J: Hello?
Ken:<i> Is Angela Kane here?</i>

00:03.004 --> 00:04.337
<i> I'm her parole officer,</i>

00:04.339 --> 00:05.871
<i> and it's been two weeks</i>
<i> since she's checked in.</i>

00:05.873 --> 00:07.072
What else are you
hiding from us, J?

00:07.074 --> 00:09.008
Pope:
He has a bowling alley.

00:09.010 --> 00:10.543
All that weight you're holding
at the house,

00:10.545 --> 00:11.810
you should stash it here.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.746
We can't hold onto
the product anymore.

00:13.748 --> 00:15.080
It's gonna cost you.

00:15.082 --> 00:17.016
Frankie could help us
fence some of Smurf's shit.

00:17.018 --> 00:19.552
Last time you stole my money,
it made me look like a moron.

00:19.554 --> 00:21.420
Well, I'm sure we can
work something out.

00:21.422 --> 00:24.089
Pope: I wake up somewhere.
I don't know how I got there.

00:24.091 --> 00:27.159
I don't know how long it's been.
I get confused.

00:27.161 --> 00:29.494
♪♪

00:29.496 --> 00:32.097
[ Laughs ]

00:32.099 --> 00:33.632
Janine: I think
I need to stay put.

00:33.634 --> 00:34.767
This is home, right?

00:34.769 --> 00:36.635
Your copies of
Smurf's will.

00:36.637 --> 00:37.836
Who the hell
is Pamela Johnson?

00:37.838 --> 00:39.572
Yeah, I know.
Right?

00:39.574 --> 00:41.040
She's one of
Smurf's old pals.

00:41.042 --> 00:42.708
The will says she gets
almost everything.

00:42.710 --> 00:44.043
Pamela Johnson?

00:44.045 --> 00:45.244
We're not used to people
taking things from us.

00:45.246 --> 00:46.912
We take things
from other people.

00:46.914 --> 00:50.182
You ain't gonna take
a goddamn thing from me.

00:50.184 --> 00:52.785
But I might
let you earn it.

00:54.188 --> 00:57.923
♪♪

00:57.925 --> 01:02.295
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:03.864 --> 01:07.600
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:07.602 --> 01:10.269
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:10.271 --> 01:13.338
♪♪

01:13.340 --> 01:19.278
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:19.280 --> 01:22.881
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:22.883 --> 01:25.818
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:25.820 --> 01:29.822
♪♪

01:29.824 --> 01:32.557
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:32.559 --> 01:36.229
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:36.231 --> 01:40.299
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:40.301 --> 01:44.036
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:44.038 --> 01:48.173
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:48.175 --> 01:51.777
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:51.779 --> 01:54.113
♪ Got a ♪

01:54.115 --> 01:56.415
[ Waves crashing ]

01:58.185 --> 02:02.321
Pastor: Christ came and died
so we could have new life.

02:02.323 --> 02:05.424
So we don't carry
the burden of our sin.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.961
We could be washed clean
of everything.

02:10.331 --> 02:11.831
Made new.

02:12.733 --> 02:14.033
John: Pope?

02:16.070 --> 02:18.737
Man, it's good to see you.
When'd you get out?

02:18.873 --> 02:20.873
A few years ago.

02:20.875 --> 02:23.542
It's been
18 months for me.

02:23.544 --> 02:26.411
Submerging yourself
in the water

02:26.413 --> 02:29.315
is a declaration of
an internal change.

02:30.151 --> 02:32.885
Decide today
for a new life.

02:32.887 --> 02:34.619
Are we ready?

02:34.621 --> 02:35.821
Woman: Yeah.

02:35.823 --> 02:37.757
Then let's go.

02:41.762 --> 02:44.163
Thinking about getting
baptized today?

02:45.700 --> 02:48.167
I don't know.

02:48.169 --> 02:49.836
What brings you
out here?

02:52.974 --> 02:54.540
A lot of things.

02:57.979 --> 02:59.111
I heard about Ang.

02:59.113 --> 03:00.846
I know she used to run
with your sister.

03:00.848 --> 03:02.982
Did you know her well?

03:02.984 --> 03:05.584
Angela?

03:05.586 --> 03:07.652
What about Angela?

03:07.654 --> 03:09.522
She passed away, bro.

03:09.524 --> 03:14.659
♪♪

03:14.661 --> 03:16.996
What?

03:16.998 --> 03:18.263
When?

03:18.265 --> 03:19.532
It was a
couple days ago.

03:19.534 --> 03:22.001
What?

03:22.003 --> 03:24.603
[ Breathing heavily ]

03:24.605 --> 03:27.406
♪♪

03:27.408 --> 03:29.342
What happened?

03:29.344 --> 03:30.943
Hey, man, she's with
our Lord and Savior now.

03:30.945 --> 03:33.078
What happened?!

03:33.080 --> 03:35.280
They found her in that
old squat up on Central.

03:35.282 --> 03:37.482
S-Someone beat her
to death.

03:37.484 --> 03:39.352
♪♪

03:39.354 --> 03:40.820
Who?

03:42.489 --> 03:44.023
I heard Shane might
have been there...

03:44.025 --> 03:45.891
Sh--
...but I don't know
for sure.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.292
I thought he was
doing 10 to 20.

03:47.294 --> 03:49.628
Well, I guess
he got out.

03:49.630 --> 03:51.296
[ Sniffs ]

03:51.298 --> 03:52.497
Hey, I'm sorry, man.

03:52.499 --> 03:54.967
Is Shane staying
with his sister?

03:54.969 --> 03:56.569
Is he?!

03:56.571 --> 03:58.704
♪♪

03:58.706 --> 04:00.706
Don't go there, man.

04:00.708 --> 04:01.974
Go there.

04:03.644 --> 04:04.843
Pope!

04:04.845 --> 04:08.981
♪♪

04:08.983 --> 04:11.917
[ Back-up alarm beeping ]

04:11.919 --> 04:14.119
[ Inhales deeply ]

04:14.121 --> 04:16.189
[ Brakes squealing ]

04:24.399 --> 04:26.131
[ Spits ]

04:26.133 --> 04:27.332
[ Toothbrush clatters ]

04:27.334 --> 04:29.668
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

04:29.670 --> 04:31.937
[ Grunts, sniffs ]

04:31.939 --> 04:33.206
Hello?

04:33.208 --> 04:34.673
Pamela:
<i> It's Pamela Johnson.</i>

04:34.675 --> 04:38.010
<i> I'd like to drop by</i>
<i> the house today.</i>

04:38.012 --> 04:40.079
Uh, today?

04:40.081 --> 04:41.614
<i> I have business</i>
<i> in La Jolla.</i>

04:41.616 --> 04:43.749
<i> I'll have my family</i>
<i> with me.</i>

04:43.751 --> 04:45.217
Uh, nah.

04:45.219 --> 04:47.686
Today's not --
not good.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.021
<i> Make it good.</i>

04:49.023 --> 04:50.389
[ Sighs ]

04:52.893 --> 04:54.093
Uh, I don't even
live there.

04:54.095 --> 04:55.294
It's my, uh --

04:55.296 --> 04:57.562
It's my brother
and my nephew.

04:57.564 --> 04:59.632
<i> Let them know I'll be there</i>
<i> around 11:00.</i>

05:03.104 --> 05:05.370
<i> You still there?</i>

05:05.372 --> 05:06.839
Yeah.

05:06.841 --> 05:08.373
<i> I'll bring lunch.</i>

05:08.375 --> 05:11.444
[ Scoffs ]
Listen, I don't even --
[ Click ]

05:11.446 --> 05:12.678
Hello?

05:13.915 --> 05:16.982
[ Door opens, closes ]

05:16.984 --> 05:19.852
[ Nick cooing ]

05:19.854 --> 05:21.920
Hi.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.256
Hello, baby.

05:26.661 --> 05:28.060
Hi, big boy!

05:28.062 --> 05:30.529
[ Gasps ]
What you got there?

05:30.531 --> 05:31.930
Hi.

05:31.932 --> 05:34.333
I thought you were supposed to
be back an hour ago.

05:36.671 --> 05:39.272
Traffic.

05:39.274 --> 05:41.340
I missed you.
Have you missed me?

05:41.342 --> 05:42.942
Have you been
sleeping for Daddy?

05:42.944 --> 05:45.410
No, he hasn't.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.280
Well, when was
his last bottle?

05:47.282 --> 05:50.149
Couple hours ago.
How was Reno?

05:50.151 --> 05:53.218
Maya's fiancé is a
50-year-old rich douchebag,

05:53.220 --> 05:55.888
but some of her other friends
are cool.

05:55.890 --> 05:57.356
50?
Mm-hmm.

05:57.358 --> 06:00.293
At least we stayed at
an insane place on the lake.

06:00.295 --> 06:02.295
The guy's in real estate,
so we had a chef

06:02.297 --> 06:05.030
and a weed bar and --

06:05.032 --> 06:06.765
Has he pooped yet?

06:06.767 --> 06:08.367
Yeah, twice.

06:08.369 --> 06:11.370
First time was about five
seconds after I changed him.

06:11.372 --> 06:12.972
[ Cellphone chimes ]

06:12.974 --> 06:14.507
You know, uh,
Maya thinks

06:14.509 --> 06:16.509
I'd be really good
at selling real estate.

06:16.511 --> 06:18.777
Says her fiancé
can set me up

06:18.779 --> 06:21.714
with some broker he knows
down in San Diego.

06:21.716 --> 06:24.183
You know, you're hot.
You know how to sell shit.

06:24.185 --> 06:25.784
Be great for you.

06:25.786 --> 06:30.255
[ Scoffs ] Big difference
between selling condos and coke.

06:30.257 --> 06:31.724
What, making a
shit-ton of money

06:31.726 --> 06:33.258
and not having to worry
about getting busted?

06:33.260 --> 06:35.794
No, I'd just have to worry
about some rich banker

06:35.796 --> 06:38.731
in Corona del Mar
grabbing my ass, but, yeah.

06:38.733 --> 06:40.666
Holy shit.

06:40.668 --> 06:41.800
What?

06:41.802 --> 06:45.804
The lady that Smurf gave all
our shit to is coming today.

06:45.806 --> 06:48.741
Deran says we're supposed to
meet her at the house.

06:48.743 --> 06:49.942
Now?

06:49.944 --> 06:51.143
Yep, now.

06:51.145 --> 06:56.949
♪♪

06:56.951 --> 06:59.151
I don't know
how you do it.

06:59.153 --> 07:00.886
You don't look
at their face.

07:00.888 --> 07:02.154
Just focus
on their tits.

07:02.156 --> 07:05.424
[ Laughter ]

07:05.426 --> 07:07.292
Well, we gotta
get out of here.

07:07.294 --> 07:08.361
Patrick: Madigan
watches the clock

07:08.363 --> 07:10.095
like our check comes
out of his pocket.

07:10.097 --> 07:12.231
[ Gasps ]
Sorry.

07:12.233 --> 07:13.832
Sorry about that,
sweetheart.

07:13.834 --> 07:15.368
♪<i> The whole world's</i>
<i> out of sync</i> ♪

07:15.370 --> 07:18.103
It's okay, Andrew.
It was an accident.

07:18.105 --> 07:20.039
♪<i> Been running so hard</i> ♪

07:20.041 --> 07:23.042
♪<i> When what I need is</i>
<i> to unwind</i> ♪

07:23.044 --> 07:25.778
♪<i> The voice of reason</i> ♪
Damn it. Again.

07:25.780 --> 07:27.112
They stiff you?

07:27.114 --> 07:29.314
♪<i> Is one I left so far behind</i> ♪

07:29.316 --> 07:32.785
♪<i> I waited so long</i> ♪

07:32.787 --> 07:35.188
If they've got enough
money to pay hookers,

07:35.190 --> 07:36.855
they've got enough
money to tip you.

07:36.857 --> 07:39.925
He was talking about that
at breakfast?

07:39.927 --> 07:43.863
Cops? They'll talk about
anything, anywhere.

07:43.865 --> 07:45.064
Yeah.

07:45.066 --> 07:46.599
I do feel
for Jerry, though.

07:46.601 --> 07:48.200
♪<i> Can't stop myself,</i>
<i> outta control</i> ♪

07:48.202 --> 07:49.602
This one?
Yeah.

07:49.604 --> 07:53.138
His wife just took off,
and his mom has cancer.

07:53.140 --> 07:54.507
So...

07:56.477 --> 07:58.077
Hey, I'll cover them
this time.

07:58.079 --> 07:59.412
No, no, it's oka--
Yeah.

07:59.414 --> 08:00.813
Unh-unh.
You don't have to do that.

08:00.815 --> 08:02.214
Just take it.

08:02.216 --> 08:04.617
♪♪

08:04.619 --> 08:06.085
Thank you.

08:06.087 --> 08:14.159
♪♪

08:14.161 --> 08:22.101
♪♪

08:22.103 --> 08:23.502
Deran:
Is Pope here yet?

08:23.504 --> 08:25.638
No.

08:25.640 --> 08:27.039
Put the guns
in the safe.

08:27.041 --> 08:28.774
Do you think she's gonna want
to walk through the house?

08:28.776 --> 08:31.244
I have no idea.
This is bullshit.

08:31.246 --> 08:33.979
She can't just call
and show up.

08:33.981 --> 08:36.048
Tenants are supposed to
have a 24-hours notice.

08:36.050 --> 08:37.250
What are you talking
about tenants?

08:37.252 --> 08:38.917
Renters, whatever.
I don't know.

08:38.919 --> 08:41.454
We agreed that we were gonna
go through the lawyers.

08:41.456 --> 08:42.921
Yeah, well, I didn't want
to wait any longer.

08:42.923 --> 08:44.990
You should have asked us
before you reached out to her.

08:44.992 --> 08:46.325
And why is that?

08:46.327 --> 08:48.193
'Cause you're the one that has
to make all the decisions now?

08:48.195 --> 08:49.394
Is that it, J?

08:49.396 --> 08:50.929
We have to
make a deal, man.

08:50.931 --> 08:52.197
What kind of deal?

08:52.199 --> 08:53.732
Look, she wouldn't come
all the way down here

08:53.734 --> 08:55.134
if she didn't want to
work something out.

08:55.136 --> 08:56.535
What, one meeting and you
know her so well already?

08:56.537 --> 08:58.471
You had one
face-to-face,

08:58.473 --> 09:00.339
but you have no idea
what she actually wants.

09:00.341 --> 09:01.874
No, you know what
I do know?

09:01.876 --> 09:03.542
If this doesn't work out,
we're losing this goddamn house.

09:03.544 --> 09:05.344
That's what I know,
and your ass is back out

09:05.346 --> 09:07.880
on the street again.

09:07.882 --> 09:09.081
Well, where's Pope?

09:09.083 --> 09:10.950
I don't know.
I called him.

09:10.952 --> 09:12.885
He said he was coming.

09:12.887 --> 09:14.887
[ Car horn honks ]

09:14.889 --> 09:16.289
That's her.

09:16.291 --> 09:22.295
♪♪

09:22.297 --> 09:24.297
You're okay with this?
[ Scoffs ]

09:24.299 --> 09:26.699
What, now you give a shit
about my opinion?

09:26.701 --> 09:34.707
♪♪

09:34.709 --> 09:42.515
♪♪

09:42.517 --> 09:44.183
[ Pamela
clears throat ]

09:44.185 --> 09:49.922
♪♪

09:49.924 --> 09:51.456
Deran.

09:51.458 --> 09:53.792
I'd like you meet
my son, Phoenix.

09:53.794 --> 09:55.995
What's up?
My granddaughter, Lark.

09:55.997 --> 09:57.196
Pleasure to meet you.

09:57.198 --> 09:59.532
This is Deran Cody,
Janine's son.

09:59.534 --> 10:01.934
Deran: This is my nephew J
and my brother Craig.

10:01.936 --> 10:04.203
Pleased to meet you.

10:04.205 --> 10:05.638
Julia's boy?

10:07.074 --> 10:08.807
That's right.

10:08.809 --> 10:10.209
How is she?

10:11.812 --> 10:13.679
She's dead.

10:13.681 --> 10:16.415
♪♪

10:16.417 --> 10:19.084
Sorry to hear that.

10:19.086 --> 10:20.285
Where's Andrew?

10:20.287 --> 10:21.954
He'll be here
a little later.

10:21.956 --> 10:23.822
Should we wait?

10:23.824 --> 10:26.425
Probably not.

10:26.427 --> 10:27.960
I brought lunch.

10:27.962 --> 10:31.296
Why don't you boys help Phoenix
carry it into my house?

10:31.298 --> 10:35.635
♪♪

10:41.676 --> 10:44.010
This is nice.

10:44.012 --> 10:46.812
A lot different than
the last time I saw it.

10:46.814 --> 10:48.614
Which is when?

10:48.616 --> 10:50.683
Before you were
born, baby.

10:52.220 --> 10:55.421
I'm gonna take a quick look
around, if you don't mind.

10:56.891 --> 11:00.492
Why don't you all get
some plates, set the table?

11:00.494 --> 11:02.028
I brought barbecue.

11:02.030 --> 11:05.163
Figured you boys were used to
eating out with your mother.

11:05.165 --> 11:06.699
Nah,
Smurf always cooked.

11:06.701 --> 11:07.834
Huh.

11:07.836 --> 11:10.903
When we were younger,
she couldn't boil water.

11:16.377 --> 11:17.910
[ Sighs ]

11:20.781 --> 11:22.315
You gonna help?

11:23.584 --> 11:27.453
[ Bag rustles,
containers thudding ]

11:27.455 --> 11:29.088
[ Plates rattle ]

11:33.394 --> 11:35.495
You're Phoenix Johnson,
the skater.

11:36.997 --> 11:38.864
Was.

11:38.866 --> 11:41.667
Used to have your deck
when I was in the 8th grade.

11:43.738 --> 11:45.804
Used to hang out with Tony Hawk
and his crew, right?

11:45.806 --> 11:48.140
If you still got the deck,
it's probably worth some money.

11:48.142 --> 11:50.409
Nah, I broke it
on a, uh, 12-stair rail

11:50.411 --> 11:52.344
when I was like 14.

11:52.346 --> 11:53.612
Too bad.

11:53.614 --> 11:56.282
What does your mom plan
to do with this place?

11:56.284 --> 11:58.150
I don't know.

11:58.152 --> 12:00.887
A mid-century modern
like this in LA...
She don't tell me shit.

12:00.889 --> 12:03.422
...would go for $4 million.
Is that your daughter?

12:03.424 --> 12:05.491
My niece.

12:05.493 --> 12:07.893
My sister's kid.
Pamela: Always wanted
a sunken living room.

12:07.895 --> 12:10.496
I'm gonna go
show them around.

12:10.498 --> 12:13.099
She had good taste.

12:13.101 --> 12:15.567
Did well for herself.

12:15.569 --> 12:17.636
Yeah, it's a little
old-fashioned.

12:17.638 --> 12:20.973
I would
get rid of those

12:20.975 --> 12:23.709
and open it up a little bit
for some more seating

12:23.711 --> 12:25.577
and some big sofas.

12:25.579 --> 12:27.780
Pamela: Mm-hmm.

12:27.782 --> 12:29.782
Think we like it
the way it is.

12:32.052 --> 12:33.986
Should we eat?

12:33.988 --> 12:35.521
Think we should get around
to whatever the hell it is

12:35.523 --> 12:37.723
you came here for.

12:37.725 --> 12:39.425
Hope you like ribs.

12:46.534 --> 12:53.339
♪♪

12:53.341 --> 12:55.607
Andrew.

12:55.609 --> 12:58.544
It's Auntie Birdie.

12:58.546 --> 13:00.479
Remember me?

13:00.481 --> 13:01.714
You know her?

13:03.818 --> 13:06.685
I don't --
It was a long time ago.

13:06.687 --> 13:08.420
♪♪

13:08.422 --> 13:10.288
It's good to see you.

13:10.290 --> 13:13.559
♪♪

13:13.561 --> 13:15.428
Yeah, I remember.

13:17.165 --> 13:18.798
I remember you.

13:20.568 --> 13:22.901
Remember Phoenix?

13:22.903 --> 13:24.837
He used to babysit
you and Julia

13:24.839 --> 13:26.839
when you were small.

13:26.841 --> 13:28.240
What's up, man?

13:28.242 --> 13:33.779
♪♪

13:33.781 --> 13:36.315
Why don't we eat?

13:36.317 --> 13:37.716
Then we'll talk.

13:37.718 --> 13:39.718
♪♪

13:39.720 --> 13:41.654
[ Chair scrapes ]

13:41.656 --> 13:50.329
♪♪

13:50.331 --> 13:52.398
[ Clears throat ]

13:52.400 --> 13:54.266
[ Sighs ]

13:54.268 --> 13:59.271
♪♪

13:59.273 --> 14:02.241
[ Police radio chatter ]

14:04.945 --> 14:07.479
Do you think
this is a good plan?

14:07.481 --> 14:09.015
Yes.
Julia: Can I help?

14:09.017 --> 14:11.817
Sure, baby.
Come here.

14:11.819 --> 14:15.888
If you hear "Jerry"
or "Madigan,"

14:15.890 --> 14:17.423
you put your hand up.

14:17.425 --> 14:19.425
Woman:<i> All officers respond</i>
<i> to 232 Ocean.</i>

14:19.427 --> 14:22.094
<i> We need coverage on Marker 6,</i>
<i> Vandergift Road.</i>

14:22.096 --> 14:23.629
What do we need a cop for,
again, in the first place?

14:23.631 --> 14:24.830
Da-da-da.

14:24.832 --> 14:26.832
Man:
<i> 10-4, Car 52 responding.</i>

14:26.834 --> 14:28.567
Woman:<i> Thanks, Jerry.</i>
[ Gasps ] Jerry!

14:28.569 --> 14:30.436
Yes, I heard!

14:30.438 --> 14:32.438
Can I help, too?

14:32.440 --> 14:34.773
Everyone helps, baby.

14:34.775 --> 14:36.775
We're going to go
for a ride.

14:36.777 --> 14:38.811
I have jobs
for both of you.

14:40.448 --> 14:41.914
What do you say,
Uncle Jake?

14:41.916 --> 14:45.517
Are you gonna help us,
or are ya chickenshit?

14:45.519 --> 14:47.053
[ Laughs ]
Bawk.

14:47.055 --> 14:50.089
[ All clucking ]

14:57.131 --> 14:59.031
So, let's talk.

15:01.402 --> 15:03.035
I have a proposal.

15:06.807 --> 15:09.808
Your mother did
very well for herself.

15:09.810 --> 15:11.744
Her properties
and her assets

15:11.746 --> 15:13.879
are worth millions
of dollars.

15:13.881 --> 15:15.614
What's your proposal?
[ Sighs ]

15:15.616 --> 15:16.882
I'm prepared
to let you start

15:16.884 --> 15:20.018
earning back
your mother's estate.

15:20.020 --> 15:21.954
How?

15:21.956 --> 15:25.157
There's a job I need done,
and knowing your mother,

15:25.159 --> 15:28.761
I suspect you all have
the skills to do it.

15:28.763 --> 15:30.562
What's the job?
[ Sighs ]

15:30.564 --> 15:33.900
There's an individual who has
something of great value to me,

15:33.902 --> 15:36.702
and I want you to
get it from him.

15:36.704 --> 15:38.170
So, you want us
to steal it?

15:38.172 --> 15:39.838
Mm-hmm.

15:39.840 --> 15:41.107
What is it?

15:41.109 --> 15:44.310
It's a safe.
And what's in it?

15:44.312 --> 15:47.179
Something he would
rather not part with.

15:47.181 --> 15:48.714
We need to know
what's in it.

15:48.716 --> 15:50.248
[ Chuckles ]
The less you know, the better.

15:50.250 --> 15:51.650
No, we need to know
what's in it,

15:51.652 --> 15:52.851
or we're not gonna
do the job.

15:52.853 --> 15:54.052
That's your decision.

15:54.054 --> 15:56.989
This is the opportunity
I'm offering.

15:56.991 --> 15:58.857
There won't be another.

15:58.859 --> 16:02.461
♪♪

16:02.463 --> 16:03.862
You want this house?

16:03.864 --> 16:05.664
Your mother's apartments?

16:05.666 --> 16:07.600
[ Chuckles ]
Her investments?

16:07.602 --> 16:09.668
We can contest
the will.

16:09.670 --> 16:11.870
You don't have
much of a case.

16:11.872 --> 16:13.139
Janine was of
sound mind.

16:13.141 --> 16:14.873
No, she wasn't.

16:14.875 --> 16:18.410
[ Breathing heavily ]

16:18.412 --> 16:22.214
♪♪

16:22.216 --> 16:27.286
Smurf had cancer.
She was very sick.

16:27.288 --> 16:29.287
Lot of pain meds,
drinking heavily --

16:29.289 --> 16:30.823
That doesn't make her
incompetent.

16:30.825 --> 16:33.025
The law says otherwise.
If you can prove it.

16:33.027 --> 16:36.963
We were named in the will.
We have grounds to contest.

16:36.965 --> 16:40.366
Why don't you just tell us
what's in the safe?

16:40.368 --> 16:47.974
♪♪

16:47.976 --> 16:49.908
Pamela: Excuse me.

16:49.910 --> 16:51.711
I'm gonna use
the ladies' room.

16:58.052 --> 16:59.886
20 years ago,
I was drunk.

17:01.589 --> 17:04.723
Got into a fight,
and, um...

17:04.725 --> 17:07.326
dude died.

17:07.328 --> 17:10.462
Guy who owns the company I
skated for -- Marion --

17:10.464 --> 17:13.732
said he was gonna
take care of it.

17:13.734 --> 17:16.735
He did.

17:16.737 --> 17:20.272
Kept the dude's shirt
with my blood on it...

17:20.274 --> 17:21.807
and his.

17:21.809 --> 17:23.809
Marion Wills?

17:23.811 --> 17:25.878
Demand Skate?
Yeah.

17:25.880 --> 17:27.847
So, what, he's trying
to blackmail you?

17:29.350 --> 17:30.749
My grandmother.

17:30.751 --> 17:34.553
I didn't know about it till
about eight months ago.

17:34.555 --> 17:37.823
Some of the homies heard,
uh, Marion bragging about it.

17:37.825 --> 17:39.892
Your mother, she has
plenty of people

17:39.894 --> 17:41.627
to do this shit for you.

17:41.629 --> 17:42.961
Why us?

17:42.963 --> 17:45.431
She doesn't want it to
get out in our circle,

17:45.433 --> 17:48.100
and it's hard to
find people to trust.

17:48.102 --> 17:49.501
What, you're saying
you trust<i> us?</i>

17:49.503 --> 17:51.169
No.

17:51.171 --> 17:52.705
I'm just saying
that you're motivated.

17:52.707 --> 17:55.841
We do this for you,
we get Smurf's estate back?

17:55.843 --> 17:57.910
Yeah, it's a step
in the right direction.

17:59.780 --> 18:01.513
You tried negotiating
with Marion?

18:01.515 --> 18:05.317
You even tried to
get your shit back?

18:05.319 --> 18:07.720
He doesn't even know
that I know.

18:07.722 --> 18:09.922
What else is
in this safe?

18:09.924 --> 18:11.657
Is there something that
we need to know about?

18:11.659 --> 18:13.392
We have no idea.

18:14.462 --> 18:15.994
We'll think about it.

18:15.996 --> 18:20.733
If we go to court,
you lose,

18:20.735 --> 18:23.469
and my grandmother is not
a patient woman.

18:23.471 --> 18:25.338
She won't ask again.

18:28.676 --> 18:31.277
[ Footsteps approaching ]

18:31.279 --> 18:34.180
[ Whispering indistinctly ]

18:37.752 --> 18:39.352
Pamela: Andrew.

18:41.422 --> 18:49.227
♪♪

18:49.229 --> 18:51.430
It's been a long time.

18:51.432 --> 18:57.236
♪♪

18:57.238 --> 18:59.305
You still smell
the same.

18:59.307 --> 19:02.108
♪♪

19:02.110 --> 19:04.710
I was very sorry
to hear about Julia.

19:04.712 --> 19:07.045
♪♪

19:07.047 --> 19:09.915
What happened?

19:09.917 --> 19:13.385
She OD'd.

19:13.387 --> 19:16.122
Must've been hard
on your mother.

19:16.124 --> 19:17.990
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:17.992 --> 19:21.460
To lose a child --
My mother didn't give
a shit about any of us,

19:21.462 --> 19:23.930
especially Julia.

19:23.932 --> 19:30.869
♪♪

19:30.871 --> 19:37.743
♪♪

19:37.745 --> 19:38.945
Craig:
Where are you going?

19:38.947 --> 19:40.479
Pope: I got
something to do.

19:40.481 --> 19:45.751
♪♪

19:45.753 --> 19:47.619
You heard my proposal.

19:47.621 --> 19:50.957
You've got 24 hours to decide
what you want to do.

19:50.959 --> 19:56.628
Yes, and Phoenix will give you
all the details you need.

19:56.630 --> 19:58.430
No...

19:58.432 --> 20:01.367
I want you out of this house
by the end of the week.

20:01.369 --> 20:02.969
♪♪

20:02.971 --> 20:04.370
Your choice.

20:04.372 --> 20:11.710
♪♪

20:11.712 --> 20:19.252
♪♪

20:22.857 --> 20:24.390
So, are we gonna
do this?

20:24.392 --> 20:25.924
Well, there's no guarantee
that we get the house back.

20:25.926 --> 20:27.125
You heard her.
"It's a start."

20:27.127 --> 20:28.394
And you heard
the granddaughter.

20:28.396 --> 20:30.196
Theres no way we're
gonna win in court.

20:30.198 --> 20:31.797
We don't know that.
We should talk to the lawyer.

20:31.799 --> 20:33.199
And what do you want
to say to her?

20:33.201 --> 20:35.868
That we had someone lie
on the death certificate

20:35.870 --> 20:37.403
after you shot Smurf
in the head?

20:37.405 --> 20:39.338
I'm just saying that we don't
know this Pamela woman.

20:39.340 --> 20:41.807
We could do this job, and then
she could call the cops on us.

20:41.809 --> 20:43.009
And why would she
do that?

20:43.011 --> 20:45.244
The house
is already hers.

20:49.083 --> 20:51.083
I say we drive up there
and scout it.

20:51.085 --> 20:52.685
When?
Tomorrow.

20:52.687 --> 20:55.688
I have to meet Frankie
with the fence.

20:55.690 --> 20:58.624
Me and J will do it.

20:58.626 --> 21:00.026
[ Inhales deeply ]

21:00.028 --> 21:02.061
This is how we get
our shit back.

21:04.164 --> 21:07.833
♪<i> You might think I'm foolish</i> ♪

21:07.835 --> 21:09.902
♪<i> Or maybe it's untrue</i> ♪

21:09.904 --> 21:11.237
[ Engine rumbling ]

21:11.239 --> 21:15.173
♪<i> You might think I'm crazy</i> ♪

21:15.175 --> 21:16.909
♪<i> All I want is you</i> ♪

21:16.911 --> 21:18.577
All right.

21:18.579 --> 21:20.246
Remember what you're
supposed to say?

21:20.248 --> 21:21.914
♪<i> You might think</i>
<i> it's hysterical</i> ♪

21:21.916 --> 21:23.049
What about you?

21:23.051 --> 21:24.917
♪<i> But I know when you're weak</i> ♪

21:24.919 --> 21:27.119
Exactly. Let's go.

21:27.121 --> 21:30.256
♪<i> You think you're</i>
<i> in the movies</i> ♪

21:30.258 --> 21:31.724
♪<i> And everything's so deep</i> ♪

21:31.726 --> 21:33.526
Hi.
Hi, there.

21:33.528 --> 21:35.193
Do you have your ticket?

21:35.195 --> 21:36.462
Yes.

21:36.464 --> 21:38.064
♪♪

21:38.066 --> 21:40.666
Sorry, hold on.
It's gotta be here somewhere.

21:40.668 --> 21:41.934
Uh...

21:41.936 --> 21:43.001
♪<i> You might think it's foolish</i> ♪

21:43.003 --> 21:44.937
Do you have the ticket?

21:44.939 --> 21:46.873
No, darling,
I gave it to you.

21:46.875 --> 21:49.275
Hold on.
[ Chuckles ]

21:49.277 --> 21:51.744
Definitely gotta
be here somewhere.

21:51.746 --> 21:52.745
[ Whispers ] Sorry.

21:52.747 --> 21:55.814
♪<i> All I want is you</i> ♪

21:55.816 --> 21:56.882
I think I lost it.

21:56.884 --> 21:58.284
That's okay.
What's your room number?

21:58.286 --> 22:00.486
We're just visiting
my mother.

22:00.488 --> 22:02.220
My grandma's
in town!

22:02.222 --> 22:04.423
The other guy parked us
just over there.

22:04.425 --> 22:06.158
Are we gonna
miss the movie?

22:06.160 --> 22:08.761
Uh, we might, baby,
if we can't get our car.

22:08.763 --> 22:10.897
It's a red Firebird.

22:10.899 --> 22:12.898
[ Sighs ]

22:12.900 --> 22:14.901
♪♪

22:14.903 --> 22:16.302
Go on.

22:16.304 --> 22:17.836
Hey, thank you
so much.

22:17.838 --> 22:19.171
Thank you.

22:19.173 --> 22:20.706
Thanks, man.
Oh, thank you.

22:20.708 --> 22:29.782
♪♪

22:29.784 --> 22:31.951
[ Engine starts, revs ]

22:44.598 --> 22:45.397
[ Engine stops ]

22:45.399 --> 22:48.234
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:00.548 --> 23:05.818
♪♪

23:05.820 --> 23:11.223
♪♪

23:11.225 --> 23:12.625
Isn't that Pope?

23:15.296 --> 23:16.496
Hey!

23:17.765 --> 23:18.897
Hey!

23:18.899 --> 23:25.437
♪♪

23:25.439 --> 23:26.639
Move, move!

23:26.641 --> 23:28.040
[ Grunts ]

23:28.042 --> 23:36.915
♪♪

23:36.917 --> 23:45.791
♪♪

23:45.793 --> 23:54.867
♪♪

23:54.869 --> 24:03.742
♪♪

24:03.744 --> 24:04.943
[ Grunts ]

24:04.945 --> 24:14.152
♪♪

24:14.154 --> 24:23.562
♪♪

24:23.564 --> 24:25.097
[ Grunts ]

24:25.099 --> 24:32.638
♪♪

24:32.640 --> 24:39.645
♪♪

24:39.647 --> 24:41.047
Watch out!
Get out of the way!

24:41.049 --> 24:43.049
Watch out! Hey!
Hey!

24:43.051 --> 24:44.917
Man: Stop, man!
What are you doing?!

24:44.919 --> 24:47.853
♪♪

24:47.855 --> 24:50.989
Whoa!
[ Grunts ]

24:50.991 --> 24:52.725
Shit!
[ Grunts ]

24:52.727 --> 24:54.861
♪♪

24:54.863 --> 24:57.463
It wasn't me, I swear!

24:57.465 --> 24:59.866
I didn't touch Angela!
[ Grunts ]

24:59.868 --> 25:06.072
♪♪

25:06.074 --> 25:08.074
[ Grunting ]

25:08.076 --> 25:12.745
♪♪

25:12.747 --> 25:15.548
I didn't do anything, bro.
What's your deal?

25:15.550 --> 25:17.549
♪♪

25:17.551 --> 25:19.085
Ohh!

25:19.087 --> 25:21.687
[ Groaning ]

25:21.689 --> 25:23.021
Leave me alone!

25:23.023 --> 25:28.160
♪♪

25:28.162 --> 25:30.228
I swear to God, dude,
please.

25:30.230 --> 25:31.630
You were there!
[ Grunts ]

25:31.632 --> 25:33.565
Why didn't you
help her?!

25:33.567 --> 25:35.367
Huh?!

25:35.369 --> 25:37.436
[ Grunts ] Why didn't
you stop her?!

25:37.438 --> 25:38.904
Why didn't you
help her?!

25:38.906 --> 25:41.707
[ Grunting ]

25:41.709 --> 25:44.042
Why didn't you
help her?!

25:44.044 --> 25:45.978
Smurf!

25:45.980 --> 25:47.313
Smurf.

25:47.315 --> 25:49.181
Why didn't you
help her?!

25:49.183 --> 25:50.716
Why didn't you
help her?!

25:50.718 --> 25:52.785
Smurf!

25:52.787 --> 25:55.988
Julia.

25:55.990 --> 25:57.990
Smurf...

25:57.992 --> 25:59.391
Ju...

25:59.393 --> 26:01.860
Why didn't you help her?
Smurf.

26:01.862 --> 26:10.736
♪♪

26:10.738 --> 26:15.141
[ Coughing ]

26:19.280 --> 26:27.820
♪♪

26:27.822 --> 26:32.825
♪♪

26:32.827 --> 26:34.293
We're good.

26:34.295 --> 26:35.894
Marion's not around.

26:35.896 --> 26:43.702
♪♪

26:43.704 --> 26:51.444
♪♪

26:51.446 --> 26:53.779
♪ Rest easy, Nipsey Hussle,
I get it ♪

26:53.781 --> 26:55.648
♪ For real,
everything prolific ♪

26:55.650 --> 26:57.249
♪ I promise to take
what I done learned ♪

26:57.251 --> 26:58.784
♪ And turn it
to a hunnid Milly ♪

26:58.786 --> 27:00.319
♪ Got my people on my back
so those I love... ♪

27:00.321 --> 27:02.788
Deran: So, who's actually
allowed to skate here?

27:02.790 --> 27:04.323
Invite only.

27:04.325 --> 27:06.592
Shop's open to
the public, though.

27:06.594 --> 27:08.861
Offices are up there.

27:08.863 --> 27:11.864
♪ Get ready, get ready,
get ready, get ready ♪

27:11.866 --> 27:13.332
Where's the safe?

27:13.334 --> 27:15.468
Bolted to the floor
near Marion's desk,

27:15.470 --> 27:18.337
and that room locks
from the inside.

27:18.339 --> 27:19.604
No way you can get in

27:19.606 --> 27:22.741
unless whoever's in there
lets you in.

27:22.743 --> 27:24.076
Alarm systems?

27:24.078 --> 27:25.678
Nothing special.

27:25.680 --> 27:29.348
♪♪

27:29.350 --> 27:30.883
Is this place ever empty?

27:30.885 --> 27:33.018
That's the thing --
never is.

27:33.020 --> 27:34.620
Wait, w-what do
you mean, "never"?

27:34.622 --> 27:37.623
It's a clubhouse, man.
Marion takes you in.

27:37.625 --> 27:40.593
You sleep here,
skate, smoke weed.

27:42.096 --> 27:44.029
See that kid right there?

27:44.031 --> 27:46.565
He lives here.
Straight up.

27:46.567 --> 27:49.434
♪ I'm stronger than you think,
wise than you know ♪

27:49.436 --> 27:51.570
All right, let's go
take a look out back.

27:51.572 --> 27:53.572
♪ Rebellious it won't take Nat
to turn her ♪

27:53.574 --> 27:55.574
♪ I'm kinda straight forward, I
don't leave to much to wonder ♪

27:55.576 --> 27:56.775
♪ You can try to control it,
but ♪

27:56.777 --> 27:58.844
[ Sniffs ]

27:58.846 --> 27:59.979
They do demo days here?

27:59.981 --> 28:01.914
Sure, every Saturday.

28:01.916 --> 28:03.582
Bring in the DJ,
boys skate.

28:03.584 --> 28:06.118
They drop product,
pack the place.

28:06.120 --> 28:07.987
Line's out the door.

28:12.193 --> 28:13.926
Anybody in the office?

28:13.928 --> 28:15.127
Not usually.

28:15.129 --> 28:16.795
Second floor's
chained off.

28:16.797 --> 28:19.398
Marion don't like random
people in and out of there.

28:19.400 --> 28:22.067
Besides, he's too busy
downstairs...

28:22.069 --> 28:23.536
being the man.

28:24.471 --> 28:27.340
How come you know so much
about this place?

28:27.342 --> 28:29.342
I work here.

28:29.344 --> 28:31.944
You work for the guy
who's blackmailing your mom?

28:31.946 --> 28:34.279
[ Sighs ]
Complicated.

28:34.281 --> 28:36.182
For all the bullshit...

28:37.952 --> 28:40.085
...Marion saw
something in me.

28:40.087 --> 28:42.221
He helped raise me.

28:42.223 --> 28:45.691
Just wanted to do the opposite
of anything my mom said...

28:45.693 --> 28:49.028
and I could skate.

28:49.030 --> 28:50.396
Shit happens.

28:52.433 --> 28:54.433
All right, well, we're gonna
need eyes over there,

28:54.435 --> 28:56.235
in the unit next door.

28:56.237 --> 28:57.570
Figure out who's
working there,

28:57.572 --> 28:59.238
what time they clock in,
what time they leave.

28:59.240 --> 29:01.106
Yeah, I can do that.

29:01.108 --> 29:02.841
Okay.

29:02.843 --> 29:04.310
We'll be in touch.

29:06.447 --> 29:08.847
♪ Do or don't you
want me to love you? ♪

29:08.849 --> 29:12.385
[ Janine howling ]

29:12.387 --> 29:14.587
[ Screams, laughs ]

29:14.589 --> 29:16.655
Are you having fun,
baby?!

29:16.657 --> 29:18.991
Andrew!
Mom...

29:18.993 --> 29:20.926
You're fine.
She's scared.

29:20.928 --> 29:22.728
She needs to
toughen up.

29:22.730 --> 29:26.599
♪ Well, you may be a lover,
but you ain't no dancer ♪

29:26.601 --> 29:29.001
[ Engine revving ]
♪ Look out ♪

29:29.003 --> 29:31.804
♪ Helter skelter ♪

29:31.806 --> 29:33.072
♪ Helter skelter ♪

29:33.074 --> 29:36.075
It doesn't work
if it's not tight.

29:36.077 --> 29:37.877
♪♪

29:37.879 --> 29:39.812
Aaah!
Heads-up.

29:39.814 --> 29:41.680
♪ Owww ♪

29:41.682 --> 29:46.752
♪♪

29:46.754 --> 29:49.021
[ Siren wailing ]

29:49.023 --> 29:50.689
[ Laughs ]

29:50.691 --> 29:53.092
[ Tires squealing ]

29:53.094 --> 29:54.760
Cops are coming.

29:54.762 --> 29:56.829
That's okay, baby.
I see him.

29:56.831 --> 29:58.697
Your mom's crazy.

29:58.699 --> 30:03.436
♪♪

30:03.438 --> 30:06.705
I'm not bailing you out of
jail when this doesn't work.

30:06.707 --> 30:07.973
Yeah, you are.

30:07.975 --> 30:12.845
♪♪

30:12.847 --> 30:17.516
♪♪

30:17.518 --> 30:20.920
Okay, kids,
don't say anything.

30:20.922 --> 30:22.722
Let me do
all the talking.

30:26.861 --> 30:28.928
Hi, Officer.

30:28.930 --> 30:30.263
How you doing today?

30:30.265 --> 30:33.132
Ma'am, do you know
how fast you were going?

30:33.134 --> 30:35.734
We were just having
a little bit of fun.

30:35.736 --> 30:37.136
You were doing 90.

30:38.473 --> 30:39.538
Oh.

30:39.540 --> 30:42.675
I guess a lot of fun,
then.

30:42.677 --> 30:44.477
License and
registration.

30:44.479 --> 30:46.345
I don't have
my registration.

30:46.347 --> 30:48.414
It's borrowed
from a friend.

30:50.017 --> 30:52.118
Who are you?
That's my brother.

30:57.158 --> 30:58.691
I need your ID.
Sure.

30:58.693 --> 31:00.425
Um, it's just
in the trunk.

31:00.427 --> 31:02.295
Can I get out?

31:13.908 --> 31:15.240
You're not gonna
give me a ticket

31:15.242 --> 31:17.109
in front of my kids,
are you?

31:17.111 --> 31:19.111
ID, please.

31:19.113 --> 31:20.379
Hard-ass.

31:20.381 --> 31:23.216
[ Trunk thuds ]

31:36.063 --> 31:37.863
Janine Cody.

31:37.865 --> 31:39.398
Mm-hmm.

31:39.400 --> 31:41.200
And you're Jerry.

31:43.070 --> 31:45.137
Do I know you?

31:45.139 --> 31:46.472
No.

31:47.542 --> 31:49.342
Maybe you should.

31:51.346 --> 31:55.614
Are you sure
there's no way...

31:55.616 --> 31:58.384
I can change your mind
about this, Officer?

32:02.289 --> 32:03.622
Like what?

32:03.624 --> 32:04.890
Mm...

32:04.892 --> 32:11.296
♪♪

32:11.298 --> 32:13.899
I figured
this might help...

32:13.901 --> 32:16.902
seeing as your mother's
sick and all.

32:16.904 --> 32:19.638
How do you know
about my mother?

32:19.640 --> 32:21.106
Jerry.

32:21.108 --> 32:22.708
♪♪

32:22.710 --> 32:25.844
I know a lot of things.

32:25.846 --> 32:30.649
I know you're pulling doubles
to take care of her.

32:30.651 --> 32:33.719
I know that this job
doesn't pay you enough.

32:36.257 --> 32:39.792
Maybe we can take care
of each other...

32:39.794 --> 32:42.061
now...

32:42.063 --> 32:43.729
and in the future.

32:43.731 --> 32:51.070
♪♪

32:51.072 --> 32:58.543
♪♪

32:58.545 --> 33:06.085
♪♪

33:06.087 --> 33:08.353
Hey, Frankie.

33:08.355 --> 33:10.155
Pleasure to see you.

33:10.157 --> 33:11.356
It's been a while.

33:11.358 --> 33:13.292
Oh, I've been
traveling.

33:15.229 --> 33:16.429
And you are?

33:16.431 --> 33:18.163
Craig.
He's a friend.

33:18.165 --> 33:21.000
Please, sit.

33:26.240 --> 33:27.773
[ Sighs ]

33:27.775 --> 33:29.775
So, how's Vladic, hmm?

33:29.777 --> 33:31.243
He's been asking
about you.

33:31.245 --> 33:32.812
Oh, we haven't spoken.

33:34.849 --> 33:36.048
Mm.

33:36.050 --> 33:38.383
So, what is it I can do
for you today, then?

33:38.385 --> 33:41.253
[ Inhales deeply ]
I've got some jewelry.

33:41.255 --> 33:43.922
[ Sighs ]
Not normally my thing.

33:43.924 --> 33:45.858
Yeah, me neither.
It's my mother's.

33:45.860 --> 33:49.262
Remember that Stella piece
I brought you last year?

33:49.264 --> 33:51.464
Mm.
That was him.

33:51.466 --> 33:58.737
♪♪

33:58.739 --> 34:05.544
♪♪

34:05.546 --> 34:08.413
All right, give me three days,
and I'll have a number for you.

34:08.415 --> 34:09.482
I appreciate that.

34:09.484 --> 34:10.683
And I trust
if things go well,

34:10.685 --> 34:13.552
we can continue
to do business.

34:13.554 --> 34:15.754
Hopefully,
on something, uh...

34:15.756 --> 34:17.156
a bit more substantial.

34:17.158 --> 34:20.092
Well, I guess that
depends on how you do.

34:20.094 --> 34:22.027
Hey.

34:22.029 --> 34:23.296
Stay safe, okay?

34:23.298 --> 34:24.897
Right, yeah.
I will.

34:24.899 --> 34:30.102
♪♪

34:30.104 --> 34:36.175
♪♪

34:36.177 --> 34:38.643
So, who's Vladic?

34:38.645 --> 34:41.046
He's someone I'd
prefer to avoid.

34:41.048 --> 34:42.648
Why, 'cause you owe him
money or something?

34:42.650 --> 34:43.983
Something like that.

34:43.985 --> 34:45.384
And that's why
you're squeezing us

34:45.386 --> 34:48.053
for the extra 2%
on this fence.

34:48.055 --> 34:52.057
I've had a few things
go sideways since Rahul.

34:52.059 --> 34:53.326
People talk.

34:53.328 --> 34:54.860
I'm down a few contacts,

34:54.862 --> 34:57.563
and it's harder to make
things happen that way.

34:59.534 --> 35:01.334
That sucks.

35:01.336 --> 35:02.768
Yeah.

35:04.471 --> 35:08.607
J's the one who approached me
about the fence...

35:08.609 --> 35:11.744
so why are you here?

35:11.746 --> 35:13.679
[ Chuckles ]

35:13.681 --> 35:15.414
[ Car door opens ]

35:18.553 --> 35:19.886
[ Car door closes ]

35:26.027 --> 35:31.496
♪♪

35:31.498 --> 35:33.298
I'll be okay.

35:33.300 --> 35:35.034
You sure?

35:35.036 --> 35:36.101
Yeah.

35:36.103 --> 35:39.038
But if you, you know,
have anything

35:39.040 --> 35:41.306
you want to
throw my way...

35:41.308 --> 35:48.313
♪♪

35:48.315 --> 35:55.120
♪♪

35:55.122 --> 36:01.961
♪♪

36:06.200 --> 36:07.499
So, it's fairly
straightforward.

36:07.501 --> 36:08.834
We pull up
the building plans,

36:08.836 --> 36:10.236
take the next couple weeks
to look over it all.

36:10.238 --> 36:11.570
Mm, should be
pretty simple.

36:11.572 --> 36:14.373
What, now you're thinking
this is a good idea?

36:14.375 --> 36:15.974
Well, we've got
bills to pay.

36:15.976 --> 36:19.578
Electric, gas, cable, phones,
Smurf's credit cards.

36:19.580 --> 36:23.049
Smurf's dead.
Screw the credit card companies.

36:23.051 --> 36:25.317
Just give them
to Pamela Johnson.

36:25.319 --> 36:27.185
You want to give her
another thing to point to

36:27.187 --> 36:28.254
if we go to court?

36:28.256 --> 36:30.923
Look, man, we need to
make some money.

36:30.925 --> 36:32.325
All right?

36:34.929 --> 36:36.496
I need to take a piss.

36:41.335 --> 36:43.869
Sell your condo yet?

36:43.871 --> 36:45.938
Listed, but no offers.

36:45.940 --> 36:47.740
Well, how about you
lower the price?

36:47.742 --> 36:49.875
[ Lighter clicks ]

36:49.877 --> 36:51.477
And take a loss?

36:51.479 --> 36:54.747
♪♪

36:54.749 --> 36:57.149
Take a loss on money
that you stole from us.

36:57.151 --> 36:59.952
The least you can do is put it
up on Airbnb or something.

36:59.954 --> 37:02.955
Makes it harder to move.

37:02.957 --> 37:05.357
Why don't you
rent out your place?

37:05.359 --> 37:08.561
You're still sleeping
in your bar, right?

37:08.563 --> 37:10.896
Or take a loan out
against the bar.

37:10.898 --> 37:14.166
Take a loan out on the bar that
I paid for with my own money?

37:14.168 --> 37:15.902
That I didn't steal?

37:15.904 --> 37:19.372
How about you take a loan out
on that bowling alley?

37:25.113 --> 37:26.712
[ Sighs ]

37:26.714 --> 37:29.248
[ Sighs ]
So, what do you think?

37:31.452 --> 37:33.152
It'll be easy.

37:33.922 --> 37:35.388
All right, fine.

37:36.724 --> 37:38.925
How'd it go
with the fence?

37:38.927 --> 37:40.326
Seems legit.

37:40.328 --> 37:41.994
Just gave him the jewelry
we got from Smurf's place

37:41.996 --> 37:44.062
on the Strand.

37:44.064 --> 37:46.465
Just gonna take
a few days.

37:46.467 --> 37:49.201
How's Frankie?

37:49.203 --> 37:50.803
She's fine.

37:50.805 --> 37:56.008
♪♪

37:56.010 --> 37:57.676
Whatever, man.

37:57.678 --> 37:59.745
I'm gonna go home
to my kid.

37:59.747 --> 38:05.217
♪♪

38:05.219 --> 38:10.756
♪♪

38:10.758 --> 38:12.558
[ Sighs ]

38:12.560 --> 38:16.228
♪♪

38:16.230 --> 38:18.331
[ Grunts ]

38:21.235 --> 38:22.901
[ Footsteps approaching ]

38:22.903 --> 38:24.837
Renn: Hey.

38:24.839 --> 38:26.839
Hey.

38:26.841 --> 38:28.707
How'd it go?

38:28.709 --> 38:30.308
Um...

38:30.310 --> 38:33.912
Pamela Johnson wants us to do
a job for her late next week.

38:33.914 --> 38:35.381
Why?

38:35.383 --> 38:38.250
So that maybe we can
get our stuff back.

38:38.252 --> 38:40.052
Shit.

38:40.054 --> 38:41.920
What's the job?

38:41.922 --> 38:46.859
She wants us to steal a safe
from a skate shop in LA.

38:46.861 --> 38:48.661
Sounds easy.

38:48.663 --> 38:50.329
Yeah.

38:50.331 --> 38:52.264
So, it's kind of
good news, then.

38:52.266 --> 38:55.001
I guess.

38:55.003 --> 38:57.269
Nick asleep?
Yep.

38:57.271 --> 38:58.537
Kept us up all night,

38:58.539 --> 39:00.606
so, of course,
now he's exhausted.

39:00.608 --> 39:01.807
Mm.

39:01.809 --> 39:04.810
Hey, uh, you gonna be here
for a little bit?

39:04.812 --> 39:06.879
Yeah, why?

39:06.881 --> 39:10.082
Just gotta make a run
and get some formula.

39:10.084 --> 39:12.218
You got a boob
right there.

39:13.888 --> 39:15.554
I took a bump
to stay up today,

39:15.556 --> 39:18.824
and I ran out of
frozen breast milk.

39:18.826 --> 39:21.360
[ Sighs ]

39:21.362 --> 39:22.428
What's the problem?

39:22.430 --> 39:25.163
He's not supposed to
have formula.

39:25.165 --> 39:27.766
Like, all the vitamins
and good shit for his brain

39:27.768 --> 39:29.167
is better when it
comes from you.

39:29.169 --> 39:31.637
One or two bottles
won't kill him, Craig.

39:31.639 --> 39:32.771
Promise.

39:32.773 --> 39:34.172
No, it's not even that,
it's just --

39:34.174 --> 39:35.374
It's just what?

39:35.376 --> 39:36.575
I just think
that your priorities

39:36.577 --> 39:38.444
are a little
messed up right now.

39:38.446 --> 39:41.313
♪♪

39:41.315 --> 39:42.981
What's that
supposed to mean?

39:42.983 --> 39:45.984
♪♪

39:45.986 --> 39:47.253
[ Sighs ]

39:47.255 --> 39:48.955
Look, it's been...

39:50.324 --> 39:52.991
Today kinda
sucked, okay?

39:52.993 --> 39:54.393
Yeah.

39:54.395 --> 39:56.395
I'll just go
and get the formula.

39:56.397 --> 39:58.597
♪♪

39:58.599 --> 40:00.066
I want to go.

40:00.068 --> 40:02.200
♪♪

40:02.202 --> 40:04.270
All right.

40:04.272 --> 40:05.804
All right.

40:05.806 --> 40:10.943
♪♪

40:10.945 --> 40:15.948
♪♪

40:15.950 --> 40:17.950
[ Pope sighs ]

40:25.025 --> 40:26.158
[ Drawer slams ]

40:26.160 --> 40:29.328
[ Breathing heavily ]

40:46.714 --> 40:48.381
Where you been?

40:50.518 --> 40:52.651
I'm leaving.

40:52.653 --> 40:54.052
What are you
talking about?

40:54.054 --> 40:55.521
[ Sniffs ]

40:55.523 --> 40:58.991
I have to go.

40:58.993 --> 41:01.660
We scouted the job that
Pamela wants us to do,

41:01.662 --> 41:03.362
and we need you.

41:06.534 --> 41:08.634
Hey, stop.
[ Drawer slams ]

41:10.404 --> 41:12.471
What's going on
with you?

41:12.473 --> 41:13.672
What is this?

41:13.674 --> 41:15.207
Whose blood is this?

41:15.209 --> 41:16.675
[ Breathing shakily ]

41:16.677 --> 41:19.077
Whose blood is this?

41:19.079 --> 41:21.047
I can't stay here.

41:24.552 --> 41:27.019
Talk to me.
What's going on?

41:27.021 --> 41:28.154
Pope, talk to me.

41:28.156 --> 41:30.156
I'm forgetting things...

41:30.158 --> 41:31.958
where I am.

41:31.960 --> 41:33.892
I'm waking up places.
I don't know how I got there.

41:33.894 --> 41:37.496
I don't remember
what happened.

41:37.498 --> 41:39.031
Deran: Okay.

41:39.033 --> 41:40.032
I'm confused.

41:40.034 --> 41:41.834
Okay, then, let's go
to the doctor.

41:41.836 --> 41:43.502
We'll talk to a doctor.
We'll see what they say.

41:43.504 --> 41:45.571
They picked me up at
some trailer park.

41:45.573 --> 41:48.240
[ Sniffles ]
And I go back to get my truck,

41:48.242 --> 41:50.308
and they said that
I'm -- I'm wandering around,

41:50.310 --> 41:51.978
knocking on doors...

41:51.980 --> 41:54.046
[ Sniffles ]
looking for Julia.

41:54.048 --> 41:56.582
What?

41:56.584 --> 41:58.917
I'm blacking out!
I'm looking for ghosts!

41:58.919 --> 42:00.118
I'm hearing voices!

42:00.120 --> 42:02.521
I'm hearing Smurf's
voice in my head!

42:02.523 --> 42:06.058
Everywhere I look,
I see her everywhere!

42:06.060 --> 42:08.628
[ Breathing heavily ]

42:12.266 --> 42:15.267
[ Sobbing ]

42:15.269 --> 42:17.403
I can't stay.

42:17.405 --> 42:18.938
Hey.

42:21.609 --> 42:23.009
Listen to me.

42:23.011 --> 42:25.077
If you want to go,
you can go.

42:25.079 --> 42:27.613
I get it, all right?

42:27.615 --> 42:32.218
I mean, you know, you've had
our backs for so long.

42:32.220 --> 42:35.354
Now we have yours, okay?

42:35.356 --> 42:37.623
You just -- You just go
do what you need to do,

42:37.625 --> 42:39.492
and then you come back,
all right?

42:42.096 --> 42:43.763
I don't think
I can come back.

42:46.434 --> 42:47.967
Pope.

42:55.243 --> 42:56.609
[ Truck door closes ]

42:59.447 --> 43:00.913
Hey, kids.

43:02.316 --> 43:03.816
Come here.

43:05.453 --> 43:06.652
All right.

43:06.654 --> 43:09.055
[ Money rustling ]

43:09.057 --> 43:10.857
These...

43:10.859 --> 43:12.791
are for you.

43:12.793 --> 43:14.660
For what?

43:14.662 --> 43:16.328
It's your cut.

43:16.330 --> 43:19.065
You helped
on a job today.

43:19.067 --> 43:21.534
When you help,
you get paid.

43:21.536 --> 43:23.535
Right?

43:23.537 --> 43:25.537
Can we go to 7-Eleven?

43:25.539 --> 43:28.407
Sure, you can!
Go on, get.

43:28.409 --> 43:29.976
Stay together!

43:33.147 --> 43:34.280
[ Sighs ]

43:34.282 --> 43:36.415
You shouldn't be
teaching them that.

43:36.417 --> 43:37.483
Why not?

43:37.485 --> 43:40.419
It's a family business.

43:40.421 --> 43:42.020
It was risky.

43:42.022 --> 43:44.924
Fortune favors
the bold, Jake.

43:50.298 --> 43:52.965
Whoo!
[ Chuckles ]

43:52.967 --> 43:55.034
[ Lighter clicks ]
What are we doing?

43:56.304 --> 43:59.105
What do you mean?

43:59.107 --> 44:02.108
You and me.
[ Chuckles ]

44:02.110 --> 44:04.143
Why don't you ask
your wife that?

44:09.450 --> 44:11.049
You need to relax.

44:11.051 --> 44:13.119
Here, have some of this.

44:19.059 --> 44:21.193
You know...

44:21.195 --> 44:24.196
you can always go home,
if you want.

44:24.198 --> 44:31.269
♪♪

44:31.271 --> 44:38.144
♪♪

44:38.146 --> 44:40.546
Hey, what's up?

44:40.548 --> 44:42.748
Pope left.

44:42.750 --> 44:45.017
What do you mean?
He took off.

44:45.019 --> 44:46.819
Said he needed
some time.

44:46.821 --> 44:49.355
Probably won't be back
for a while.

44:49.357 --> 44:50.923
What about the job?

44:52.360 --> 44:53.960
We'll handle it.

44:53.962 --> 44:56.562
♪♪

44:56.564 --> 44:58.097
Where you going?

45:00.434 --> 45:01.900
I figure with Pope gone,

45:01.902 --> 45:03.903
I should probably spend
some more time at home.

45:05.173 --> 45:06.839
For what?

45:06.841 --> 45:09.307
♪♪

45:09.309 --> 45:10.709
Keep an eye on things.

45:10.711 --> 45:13.379
♪♪

45:13.381 --> 45:16.048
Your house -- You're just
gonna leave that empty?

45:16.050 --> 45:19.785
[ Sighs ] Well, maybe
I'll rent it out,

45:19.787 --> 45:21.587
like you suggested.

45:21.589 --> 45:30.196
♪♪

45:30.198 --> 45:34.500
♪♪

45:38.406 --> 45:46.812
♪♪

45:46.814 --> 45:55.221
♪♪

45:55.223 --> 46:03.729
♪♪
